<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1228,1911]" box="[189,932,1817,1842]" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Etymology. The species is named refer to the very long cerci of male.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1228,1911]" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">
Remarks. This new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Liu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2014" box="[709,1037,1852,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Phryganogryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interrupta">
<emphasis box="[709,1037,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="517">Phryganogryllacris interrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it by the head and pronotum blackish pattern and abdominal tergite 9 of male with almost truncated posterior margin.
</paragraph>
